Jean-Michel Basquiat and Madonna had a brief but intense relationship in the early 1980s  before both skyrocketed to global fame. 

They met around 1982, when Madonna was still an up-and-coming singer, and Basquiat was gaining recognition in the New York art scene. 

More in the 1st alt text 👇

images.alt:
Their relationship was passionate and tumultuous, reflective of the chaotic energy of the downtown Manhattan creative world at the time.

Basquiat introduced Madonna to the art world, and she, in turn, offered a window into the world of pop culture and music. 

According to Madonna, Basquiat was incredibly talented but also deeply troubled, struggling with drug addiction, which ultimately affected their relationship. 

When they broke up, Basquiat reportedly took back the paintings he had given her and painted over them in black.

Though short-lived, their relationship is often cited as a poignant intersection of two major cultural forces in 1980s New York.
